OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1776348651
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 21 Apr to Thu 30 Apr
OL,6,FHigh pressure to the north of the UK
OL,7,Fwill bring plenty of dry weather and
OL,8,Fsunny spells at first. A few scattered
OL,9,Fshowers are possible in central and
OL,10,Feastern areas. Parts of the east coast
OL,11,Fcould be on the chilly side with low
OL,12,Fcloud and an onshore breeze, but
OL,13,Ffurther west it will feel quite warm,
OL,14,Fespecially in sunnier areas. By the
OL,15,Fweekend, unsettled weather is
OL,16,Fsignalled to return, but confidence in
OL,17,Fthe details is low with a range of
OL,18,Fscenarios possible. One scenario is
OL,19,Ffor a northerly wind bringing wintry
OL,20,Fshowers to northern and eastern
OL,21,Fcoasts, and some snow over Scottish
OL,22,Fmountains. If this does occur it will
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fprobably not last more than a few
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fdays, before high pressure attempts to
OL,25,Freturn towards the end of the month.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1776348651
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Fri 1 May to Fri 15 May
OL,6,FChangeable weather is likely through
OL,7,Fthe period. In broad terms higher
OL,8,Fpressure is more likely to the north,
OL,9,Fwith lower pressure to the south.
OL,10,FAcross Scotland and northern half of
OL,11,FEngland this would mean drier and more
OL,12,Fsettled weather. Meanwhile, Northern
OL,13,FIreland, Wales and the southern half
OL,14,Fof England perhaps seeing a greater
OL,15,Fchance of rain or showers at times,
OL,16,Fbut plenty of scope for fair weather
OL,17,Fin between. Temperatures will probably
OL,18,Fbe close to or slightly above average
OL,19,Foverall, perhaps becoming more widely
OL,20,Fwarm at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
